com.cyc.baseclient.cycobject

Class FormulaImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyc.baseclient.cycobject.FormulaImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CycObject, Formula, Comparable<Object>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CycFormulaSentence, NautImpl

    public class FormulaImpl
extends Object
implements Formula
    A class representing CycL formulas.

    Cyc formulas may be either sentential (see CycFormulaSentence) or denotational (see NautImpl).

    A formula consists of an operator, which must be a CycObject and a sequence of arguments, which may be either CycObjects or certain primitives, notably booleans, strings, and numbers. See DefaultCycObject.isCycLObject(java.lang.Object) for syntactically valid argument types.
